ubItem><SubItem><Name>instPWM</Name><Type Namespace="CPNTeck_OSCAT_BASIC">CTRL_PWM</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Duty-cycle PWM generator (period-based)]]></Comment><BitSize>1024</BitSize><BitOffs>2624</BitOffs></SubItem><Method><Name>_PwmUpdate</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ ============================================================================
 METHOD: _PwmUpdate
 Updates OSCAT PWM_DC with enable, period and duty[%]. Returns pulse.
 NOTE: Adjust parameter names/types below if your OSCAT 'PWM_DC' signature differs.
 Common forms are: PWM_DC(EN, DC[% or 0..1], T, OUT) or (IN, DC, T, Q).
 ============================================================================]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>enable</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE: PWM active, FALSE: output low]]></Comment><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>period</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ PWM period]]></Comment><Type>TIME</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>dutyPct</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Duty [%], 0..100]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>pulse</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ PWM output (TRUE during ON time)]]></Comment><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Local><Name>dcUse</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Local></Method><Method><Name>_ErrorToDuty</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ ============================================================================
 METHOD: _ErrorToDuty
 Maps absolute error [mm] to PWM duty [%], with min/max clamps.
 duty = clamp( gain[%/mm] * absError_mm, minDuty%, maxDuty% )
 ============================================================================]]></Comment><ReturnType>REAL</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>absError_mm</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ absolute position error [mm]]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>gainPctPerMm</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ slope [% per mm]]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>minDutyPct</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ minimum duty [%]]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>maxDutyPct</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ maximum duty [%]]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Local><Name>d</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Local></Method><Method><Name>_ClampReal</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ ============================================================================
 METHOD: _ClampReal
 Returns val clamped to [lo..hi].
 ============================================================================]]></Comment><ReturnType>REAL</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>val</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>lo</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>hi</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Local><Name>v</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Local></Method><Method><Name>_InTolerance</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ ============================================================================
 METHOD: _InTolerance
 Returns TRUE when |value - target| <= tol
 ============================================================================]]></Comment><ReturnType>BOOL</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>8</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>value</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>target</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>tol</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>_DriveNone</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ ============================================================================
 METHOD: _DriveNone
 De-energize both outputs (exclusive safety).
 ============================================================================]]></Comment></Method><Method><Name>_ApplyMinOnGate</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ ============================================================================
 METHOD: _ApplyMinOnGate
 Enforces a minimum ON-time for each direction and ensures exclusivity.
 - openPulseAllowed / closePulseAllowed are the post-limit PWM pulses.
 - Once a direction output turns ON, it stays ON for at least minOnTime.
 - While one direction is ON and still within its min ON-time, the other
   direction cannot start (exclusivity).
 ============================================================================]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>openPulseAllowed</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ PWM pulse for OPEN, after limit check]]></Comment><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>closePulseAllowed</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ PWM pulse for CLOSE, after limit check]]></Comment><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>minOnTime</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Minimum ON time]]></Comment><Type>TIME</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>openingCmd</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Resulting OPEN command (after gating)]]></Comment><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Parameter><Name>closingCmd</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Resulting CLOSE command (after gating)]]></Comment><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter></Method><Properties><Property><Name>PouType</Name><Value>FunctionBlock</Value></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name>FB_FormingBoardRollUpDown</Name><Comment><![CDATA[---------------------------------------------------------------
  FB_FormingBoardRollUpDown
  Purpose:
    - Drive "Roll Up" / "Roll Down" with safety interlocks
  Behavior:
    - Fault = TRUE  -> both outputs OFF
    - Limit sensors inhibit motion toward that limit
    - If both commands are pressed simultaneously -> no motion
    - Outputs are mutually exclusive
  Notes:
    - Variable names kept exactly as provided (e.g., limitDOwnSensor)
----------------------------------------------------------------]]></Comment><BitSize>192</BitSize><SubItem><Name>rollUpCmd</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Command request to roll UP (active-high)]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>64</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rollDownCmd</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Command request to roll DOWN (active-high)]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>72</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>limitUpSensor</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE when upper limit is reached (stop further UP)]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>80</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>limitDOwnSensor</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE when lower limit is reached (stop further DOWN)]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>88</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>fault</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE = fault present -> outputs forced OFF]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>96</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rollUp</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Drive UP output (mutually exclusive with rollDown)]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>104</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rollDown</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Drive DOWN output (mutually exclusive with rollUp)]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>112</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>upAllowed</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Internal permission and arbitration flags]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>120</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>downAllowed</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>128</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bothPressed</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>136</BitOffs></SubItem><Properties><Property><Name>PouType</Name><Value>FunctionBlock</Value></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name>FB_FormingBoardWireStretchControl</Name><BitSize>832</BitSize><SubItem><Name>stretchCmd</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Jog command to stretch (increase tension)]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>64</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>unstretchCmd</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Jog command to unstretch (decrease tension)]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>72</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>limitStretchSensor</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE when at maximum stretch limit]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>80</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>limitUnstretchSensor</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE when at minimum stretch limit]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>88</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>fault</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ External fault interlock]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>96</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>stretch</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Motor output: stretch direction]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>104</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>unstretch</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Motor output: unstretch direction]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>112</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>busy</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE when motor running in any direction]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>120</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>deviceState</Name><Type>STRING(80)</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Human-readable status for HMI]]></Comment><BitSize>648</BitSize><BitOffs>128</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><Properties><Property><Name>PouType</Name><Value>FunctionBlock</Value></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name>FB_SimpleMotorStart_V2</Name><BitSize>3328</BitSize><SubItem><Name>startCommand</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Pulse to toggle run (Pulso para alternar execução)]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>64</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>stopCommand</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Pulse to force stop (Pulso para forçar parada]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>72</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>motorStarterTrip</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Softstarter healthy/ready (Softstarter ok/pronto)]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>80</BitOffs><Default><Bool>true</Bool></Default><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>safetyOK</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ External interlock 1 (Intertravamento 1)]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>88</BitOffs>