 Replace FT_PT1T with the correct type name from your OSCAT lib if different.]]></Comment><BitSize>320</BitSize><BitOffs>2944</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_ifFiltered</Name><Type>REAL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Method temp]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>3264</BitOffs></SubItem><Method><Name>_InputFilter</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ ============================================================================
 METHOD: _InputFilter
 OSCAT PT1 filter for PV, with enable/disable and bumpless behavior.
 When disabled, the filter tracks input quickly (tiny T) to avoid bumps.
 ============================================================================]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>enableFilter</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE=apply PT1, FALSE=bypass]]></Comment><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>rawValue</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Input value to be filtered]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>filterTime</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ PT1 time constant]]></Comment><Type>TIME</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>filterGainK</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ PT1 gain, typically 1.0]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>filteredValue</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Filtered (or bypassed) value]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Local><Name>kUse</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Local><Local><Name>tUse</Name><Type>TIME</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Local><Local><Name>yPT1</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Local></Method><Properties><Property><Name>PouType</Name><Value>FunctionBlock</Value></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name>FB_LevelControl_V2</Name><Comment><![CDATA[
  Change summary (minimal):
